  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:DelegateTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:MessageAgentTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:PeerClaimRegionTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:PeerNegotiateTaskTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:PeerReviewTool ;
  .

chatman:AnalysisToolCategory
  a skos:ConceptScheme ;
  rdfs:label "Process Analysis Tools"@en ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:PM4PyDiscoverTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:CodeSymbolsTool ;
  .

chatman:ManagementToolCategory
  a skos:ConceptScheme ;
  rdfs:label "Agent Management Tools"@en ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:ListAgentsTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:CreateAgentTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:ListSkillsTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:CreateSkillTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:AskUserTool ;
  skos:hasTopConcept chatman:HelpTool ;
  .

###############################################################################
# FINAL NOTES
###############################################################################

chatman:AgentOntologyNote
  rdfs:comment """
This ontology defines the semantic foundation for OSA agents. Key concepts:

1. AGENT TYPES (DUL-based):
   - chatman:AIAgent: Autonomous software entities
   - chatman:LLMAgent: Reasoning via Large Language Models (ReAct)
   - chatman:ProcessAgent: Deterministic process-based execution (YAWL)
   - chatman:SensorAgent: Monitoring and observation (SOSA)

2. ROLES (YAWL pattern responsibilities):
   - CoordinatorRole: Parallel orchestration, deadlock detection
   - WorkerRole: Task execution
   - SensorRole: State monitoring (SOSA Observation)
   - AnalyzerRole: Pattern analysis, synthesis
   - HealingRole: Failure detection + diagnosis + recovery (Armstrong + WvdA)

3. TOOL CAPABILITIES (WoT Thing Description ActionAffordances):
   - File system operations (read, write, edit, search)
   - Memory and knowledge (save, recall, search)
   - Network and integration (web, A2A, BusinessOS API)
   - Command execution (shell, git, computer use)
   - Agent coordination (delegate, message, negotiate)
   - Process analysis (PM4Py discovery)
   - Management (create agents, skills, ask user)

4. OPERATIONAL TIERS (Resource Budget Constraints):
   - Critical: <100ms, 1000 ops/min (heartbeat, consensus, healing)
   - High: <500ms, 100 ops/min (business logic)
   - Normal: <5s, 10 ops/min (background)
   - Low: <30s, 1 op/min (housekeeping)

5. EXAMPLE AGENTS:
   - OptimalSystemAgent: Coordinator for entire OSA system
   - ProcessOptimizer: Analyzes logs, proposes YAWL optimizations
   - HealingDiagnosis: Detects/diagnoses/heals failures (Armstrong + WvdA)

All tool capabilities include:
- Input schema (JSON Schema for parameters)
- Output schema (structure of results)
- Security level (public/internal/sensitive)
- Safety mode (read-only/write/execute)
- Quality metrics and constraints

This ontology is compatible with:
- PROV-O (agent actions are prov:Activity)
- W3C ORG (agents participate in org:OrganizationalUnit)
- DCAT 3 (agents consume/produce dcat:Dataset)
- SOSA (sensor agents implement sosa:Sensor)
- WoT Thing Description (tools are td:ActionAffordance)
- DUL (agents are dul:SocialAgent, roles are dul:Role)
- BFO (agents are bfo:Object, actions are bfo:Process)
"""@en ;
  .
